1. If we make any changes in webpack.config.js we need to restart your build even we are using watch.
   Watch is looking only for changes in the application source. Webpack dev server is a development server like 
   live-server but comes with some nice features specific to webpack.It is going to speed up the  process between 
   changing our application files and actually seeing those changes reflected in the browser.

2. contentBase (DevServer property) lets us tell the DevServer  where it can find our public files.

3. presets are just a collection of plugins